there. Actually, I prefer it that way.

=C2=A0

In retrospect, for example, it was nearly inevitable that Est=C3=A9e Lauder=
 Companies would get a new C.E.O., even as the group kept denying it. Rache=
l Strugatz, who joined Puck in February,
documented ( https://puck.news/and-the-next-ceo-of-estee-lauder-is/?utm_sou=
rce=3Dgoogle&utm_medium=3Dcpc&utm_campaign=3D21020658896&campaign_type=3D&c=
ampaign_id=3D21020658896&placement=3Dg&utm_content=3D&adset_id=3D1603216806=
33&utm_term=3D&gad_source=3D1&gclid=3DCj0KCQiAyc67BhDSARIsAM95Qzu5JLorfAzQy=
xfG5htbxoE5iaBb6x68kcSGe_t1SALy0R5pUbUWIigaApzpEALw_wcB&utm_campaign=3DLine=
+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F2%2F24%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBER=
S+%281%2F2%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_t=
erm=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) the entire saga, breaking all the big story deve=
lopments. She will be tracking the tenure of
St=C3=A9phane de La Faverie=E2=80=94who officially succeeded Fabrizio Freda=
 yesterday=E2=80=94closer than anyone this year.=C2=A0

Then there was my observation that off-price channels were overtaking the b=
usiness. This hypothesis was validated when the F.T.C. blocked the Tapestry=
-Capri merger on account of the ostensible threat of decreased competition =
posed by the union of Coach and Michael Kors=E2=80=99s outlet stores. LVMH =
did set out to futureproof itself for
the next phase of luxury consumption, as I predicted, although I never expe=
cted the year to be so tough for once-untouchable luxury brands like Dior a=
nd Louis Vuitton.

However, the state of normalcy I assumed everyone would be seeking after th=
e pandemic roller coaster=E2=80=A6 was never achieved. Instead, the pace of=
 designer musical chairs increased, and fashion=E2=80=99s leaders tried to =
manage the executive suite chaos. The LVMH succession sequence=E2=80=94from=
 Michael
Burke=E2=80=99s exit from the Fashion Group to the firing of H.R. head Chan=
tal Gaemperle to the promotion of family turnaround favorite Alexandre Arna=
ult=E2=80=94felt particularly jarring, but probably only because Bernard Ar=
nault is not telegraphing his master plan.

